# Development

## Core commands

```bash
pixi install
pixi run config
pixi run lint
pixi run run
```

{% if has_slurm %}`pixi run run` expands to `nextflow run . -profile slurm -resume`, and the generated config enables lenient process caching for HPC-friendly resume behavior.
{% endif %}
## Template-specific note

This project was generated from a Copier template that uses a local context hook.
If you re-render from the template, make sure Copier has `copier-templates-extensions`
available and run with `--trust`.

## Layout

- `main.nf` contains the starter DSL2 workflow.
- `conf/base.config` holds shared resource labels.
- `conf/modules.config` is reserved for process-specific overrides.
- `conf/{{ 'slurm' if has_slurm else 'local' }}.config` defines the selected executor.
